# Video: The Danger of a Single Story

#### This video builds on what we've covered regarding identity so far. Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie, the Nigerian-born author of <ins>Americanah</ins> and <ins>We Should All Be Feminists</ins>, speaks of the danger of a "single story" when it comes to understanding others.

#### Watch the following TED Talk video from <b>8:27 - 13:24 minutes</b>. While you watch, consider the following: 

### Imagine a teacher told themselves a "single story" about you as a student. 
* #### What might that story tell about you? 
* #### What does it leave out?

